HEADWORD: Bowfin
<hw>Bow"fin`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A voracious ganoid fish (<spn>Amia calva</spn>) found in the fresh
waters of the United States; the mudfish; -- called also <altname>Johnny
Grindle</altname>, and <altname>dogfish</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bowge</ent>⟦br⟧
